s origins trace back to  when walt disney licensed the image of mickey mouse for use on a childrens writing tabletchwdc  on december  of that year walt disney productions formed the walt disney enterprises wde division to handle merchandisingchwdc  the mickey mouse doll production by charlotte clark started shortly after in january chwdc  the wde division also hired george borgfeldt  company of new york as a licensing agent to make mickey and minnie mouse toyschwdc  borgfeldt  company in turn set to work developing other products granting the first license to walkburger tanner and company of st gall switzerland for mickey and minnie mouse handkerchiefschwdc  that summer of  disney expanded wde to england granting a general license to william banks levy for mickey and minnie mouse character merchandisechwdc  in  disney closed a merchandising contract with herman kay kamen for sole representationchwdc  early on wde began to show results the companys merchandising made the silly symphony film three little pigs  the companys first profitmaking animated filmchwdc  in  disney licensing expanded to handcrank toy projectorschwdc  diamondstudded mickey mouse pins mickey mouse toffee in englandchwdc  and a lionel windup train toychwdc  while a patent is received for ingersollwaterbury clock companys mickey mouse watchchwdc  yet more companies licensed the mickey mouse image general foods did so for one year and made  million on the post toasties cereal box mickey was the first licensed character on such a productchwdc  clashes with other companies werent unavoidable though disney filed suit on july  against the united biscuit company of america sawyer biscuit company and the chicago carton company for unauthorized use of disney characters for animal crackers which lasted for four months and ended in disneys favorchwdc  disney signed on july   with courvoisier galleries making courvoisier disneys original art marketing representative in december walt disney enterprises was renamed walt disney productionschwdc  in october  disney and kay kamen extend the merchandising contract but only for the americaschwdc  in  the character merchandising division is formed with in disneychwdc  also that year on october  kay kamen disneys licensing representative died in an air france plane crash over the azoreschwdc  with roy disneys split off the merchandising division from disney production jimmy johnson became head of the merchandising divisions publication department in  and took on managing business affairs for the walt disney music company disney had a food division with product from bread to soft drinks which was mostly discontinued due to its contract with abc to produce tv shows and the need to not be in competition with potential advertisers after disney purchased the rights for winnie the pooh to make a  animated short film the company conceded to a broad licensing agreement with sears roebuck  co stephen slesinger incs pati slesinger found merchandise that disney did not pay royalties on the slesinger then attempt to get the aa milne trust to abrogate its contract in  disney paid stephen slesinger inc and the milne estate to end the royalty issue and agreed to a new contract that lower slesinger incs royalty percentage in  the intergovernmental philatelic corporation of new york was licensed by walt disney productions to make disney character stamps for several countrieschwdc  historyedit disney consumer productsedit disney consumer products former type subsidiary industry merchandising fate split up predecessor character merchandising division founded  defunct  headquarters burbank california united states area served worldwide products textiles apparel and luxury goods services licensing parent disney consumer products and interactive media the walt disney company divisions licensing subsidiaries disney store website disneyconsumerproductscom disney consumer products was incorporated with the state of california in  the first disney store opened in glendale california on march  chwdc  on october  disney agreed to a licensing contract with mattel for a disney character infant and preschool toy linechwdc  dcp purchased childcraft education corp maker of childrens furniture and equipment retail stores and catalog sales from grolier inc in april nyt  in april  the th store was opened in montclair california along with the first mickeys kitchen fast food restaurantnyt  on november   mattel and disney extended the  agreement adding pinocchio bambi dumbo its a small world and the autopia to the toy linechwdc  in march  disney stores closed the two mickeys kitchen as the restaurants were only breaking even while well received by the customers as the company wanted to focus on overseas expansions in  dcp ended an exclusive licensing agreement with sears for winnie the pooh three distinct product lines were created for pooh disney pooh based on the disney redshirted tan bear cartoon version  acre collection a more upscale line for department stores and the classic pooh line based on the original aa milne books ernest h shephard illustrations dcp licensing peak in  with  disney stores worldwide operating income of  million and  licensees for mostly winnie the pooh and mickey mouse product plus some top animated moviesnyt  disneys and mcdonalds tenyear crosspromotional agreement began on january  nyt  in may  the vermont teddy bear co filed a copyright infringement suit against disney over poohgrams being similar to its mailorder beargram trademark and logo also disney enterprises inc sold dcp operating subsidiary childcraft education corp to us office products colat  in march  walt disney records and walt disney music publishing were transferred out of dcp to buena vista music group in the disney studio division by  pooh outsold mickey mouse  million to  million through november of that year in justlicensedtoy sales by replacing sears with  licensees including mattel hallmark timex tupperware and royal daulton dcp has since increased pooh product lines from  million to  billion franchise focusedit dcp office buildings in glendale at disneys grand central creative campus with mickey mouse and other characters on products everywhere and a general retail decline in  dcp had registered operating income of only  millionnyt  in december  andrew p mooney became the head of dcp he created the disney princess franchise in january nyt  he also developed the disney couture fashion line walt disney signature furniture a princessinspired bridal gowns line and lines based on the pixar films toy story and carslat  mooney had dcp try an always fresh labeled womens nightshirts and tshirts line which attempt to be more mature but failed he also reduced the number of licensees in half sold low sale stores and had staff actively pursuing licensing partners than waiting for proposals for example mooney worked to have fred segal a highend retailers sell specialty products and opened a sales office near walmarts headquarters in bentonville arkansas in  mooney lead a promotion of mickey mouse tshirts by getting them into the hands of celebrities which was a success also disney publishing issued its first original comic book witch which was successful enough to be adapted into an animated seriesnyt  consumer products also begin expanding licensing in the food category in the s dcp agreed to a licensing agreement with kellogg company for a kelloggs disney cereal line launched in february  kelloggs disney mickeys magix kelloggs disney hunny bs and kelloggs disneypixar buzz blasts in may  dcp and wells dairy launched a disneybranded dairy line with a variety of new ice creams frozen novelties and yogurt products in may  dcp licensed krogers the old yeller name to sell dog food the japanese stores were sold to oriental land company in lat  while most north american stores were sold and licensed in november  to the childrens placelat  disney licensed motorola for cordless phones and two way handset radios in august  for the first  quarters of  disney consumer products made  million in operating income placing the year ahead of  and  in may  the disney cuties design a more anime style line was introduced with tshirts mooneys major initiatives was to turn disney into a lifestyle brand by relying on the disney brand reputation instead of its characters to sell clothing and household goods with half the royalty percentage of the  for disney characters at fred segal in august the retailer was test selling snap watches with swappable faces and wristbands with disney characters with hipper urban designs in spring  dcp planned to start sell pants and jean jackets under the disney denim brand with a cartoon whimsical elementsnyt  on august   the disney dream desk pc designed by frog design and manufactured by medion began being sold at compusa and disney online dcp planned to release a camcorder and digital camera later in the year disney purchased the rights to the muppets and the bear in the big blue house franchises from the jim henson company on february  nyt  the two brands were placed under control of the muppets holding company llc then as a unit of disney consumer products in  dcp has begun working with various indian retail outlets to establish disney corners within the outlets to sell licensed merchandise also that year mooney formed the disney fairies franchise which launched in the fall with the fairy dust and the quest for the egg book in the early s disneytoon studios dts joined dcp as their internal disney conglomerate video partner in developing the new disney franchises while dcp eyed other potential franchises dts looked to the seven dwarfs for a male centric franchise to counterbalance the female centric fairies by  in  the muppets holding company was transferred from the disney consumer products unit to the walt disney studios with studio executives passing on oversight the unit was placed in the special events groupnyt  with disney princesses a success and disney fairies just under way in  consumer products started looking into the next possible franchises with disney bunnies selected already dcp in may concluded a consumer products master licensing agreement for indochina including vietnam cambodia and laos with east media holdings incs emhi licensing inc on september  the disney jeans brand was launched in india under license to indus clothing who planned to open  disney jean stores by the end of  in october dcp india franchised to ravi jaipuria corporation the rights for five years to set up  disney artist brand stores and wholesale under the disney artist brand disney character branded greeting cards stationary arts crafts and party product in india nepal sri lanka bangladesh and maldives in january  two new dcp franchises were launched disney bunnies and disney dragonkind in  disney purchased back its disney stores from the childrens placelat  on june   disney interactive studios is transferred out of dcp to the disney interactive media group john lasseter of pixar became a creative advisor to dcp in  after already assisting on cars products lasseter pushed for an end to label slapping which is using a popular move to sell unrelated generic toyslat  the disney princesses franchise has generated more than  billion in retail sales worldwidelat  in postchristmas  disney pookalooz a plush line of disney caricatures was launched with its first set at toyrus with disney stores receiving them in midmarch  with the cheshire cat selling well the muppets were considered the best sellers of the second set of pookalooz over the expected “nightmare before christmas” characters in  disney acquired marvel entertainment for  billion josh silverman a senior executive at marvel was appointed executive vice president of global licensing for disney consumer products and helped facilitate the disneymarvel integration in  disney fired marvel studios marketing department taking over marketing of their films beginning with the  film the avengers the cars sequel was approved for a  debut despite the original being panned by the critics and one of the lowest grossing pixar film as its licensed products have done welllat  mooney stepped down as dcp chair in september lat  with robert chapek being appointed president of dcp dcp expanded its responsibility to include all retailing distribution and licensing for marvel pixar video discs and video gameslat  swampy the alligator from wheres my water was the first disney interactive media group original character to get the merchandising treatment by  in  disney was the world’s largest licensor and number  in the entertainment category according to international licensing industry merchandisers’ association for another year with an  market share and  billion in march  disney sent a letter to its suppliers to have them by april  pull any disney branded products out of the five highestrisk countries bangladesh ecuador venezuela belarus and pakistan based on a world bankgoverned metric report this was announced in may after a bangladeshi factory building collapsed haiti and cambodia which are also lowranking countries were allowable per disneys new policy so long as the factories worked with the better work health and safety program run by the international labour organization and the international finance corporation bangladesh factories were liable to get work if they also partnered with the better work program disney also stated that less than  of its products were sourced from bangladesh and even less from the other four countries dcp began representing lucasfilm brands in june  with the addition of star wars disney has six of the top  franchises disney princess st star wars nd winnie the pooh rd cars th mickey  friends th and toy story th with two more in the top twenty disney fairies th and spiderman th in october dcp announced an arrangement with wet seal for an abc family character inspired crush by abc family apparel and accessories line to reach the shelves in  in april  dcp was the subject of online criticism from numerous parents through the disney stores facebook page and other forums for severely underestimating consumer demand for merchandise related to disney animations  blockbuster hit frozen dcp saw its profit increase by  for the  yearnyt  on february   robert chapek was named chairman of walt disney parks and resorts effective that daynyt  leslie ferraro formerly executive vice president of global marketing sales and travel operations of walt disney parks and resorts was named president of dcplat  dcpimedia historyedit disney consumer products and interactive media was formed in june  as merger of disney consumer products and disney interactive the presidents of dcp and dim were appointed cochairs of the division while retaining the presidency of their subsidiary while disney publishing worldwide would report to them as cochairs the units were brought together due to increase use of technology on the part of dcp with the announced playmation toy system and digital publishing by dpw in  the muppets studio was transferred then when the new division was formed ended up as a part of the newly formed dcpi labs unit on january   maker studios was placed under the control of disney interactive concurrent with the appointment of courtney holt as maker head with the title of executive vice president ferraro left disney eight months later in february  with james pitaro becoming sole chairman disney coop team was formed in  to work with licensees and other partners for branded content like disney boxed the reverse concept of unboxing with hasbro about creating a toy content  media department was formed under executive vice president andrew sugerman in early  from disney publishing worldwide disney lol oh my disney and other units maker studio was transferred into dcpi content and media in december  while former maker head moved to disney corporate strategy unit as executive vice president of media and strategy disney digital network was formed by the may   disneys digital content newfronts with maker the former disney online websites starwarscom and other digital first content units dcpi moved to address for all franchises three issues expanding the audience category expansion  product development and directtoconsumer with marvel and star wars dcpi planned to push into the female audience with star wars dcpi partnered with lucasfilm animation for star wars forces of destiny which features female characters premieres on dcpis disney youtube channel and supported by apparel books and toys including a new product type adventure figures dcpi has worked on aging up minnie mouse by working with several designers for product appealing to adults and young adults for primary the fashion field with ashley ecksteins her universe disney consumer had already work with on expanding star wars and marvel products to girls and women now her universe is working on a disney cobranded athleisure line for both sexes and disney princess franchisesedit franchises launched disney princess  disney fairies  franchises considered  disney bunnies disney dwarves disney horses disney mermaids disney trains andrew p mooney of disney consumer products dcp created the disney princess franchise in january nyt  in  mooney formed the disney fairies franchise which launched in the fall with the fairy dust and the quest for the egg book in the early s disneytoon studios dts joined dcp as their internal disney conglomerate video partner in developing the new disney franchises while consumer products eyed other potential franchises dts looked to the seven dwarfs for a malecentric franchise to counterbalance the femalecentric fairies by  the muppet franchise held by dcp in muppet holding company after being purchased in  and transferred out in  to disney studiosnyt  with disney princesses a success and disney fairies just under way in  disney consumer products started looking into the next possible franchises see table at right with disney bunnies selected already in january  two new dcp franchises were launched disney bunnies with three books and disney dragonkind with a set of statues complications relating to the production of tinker bell the debut film of the disney fairies franchise lead to discussion over the focus of disneytoon studios pixar leadership exerted control and affected franchise projects at the production company tinker bells animation was scrapped and was restarted while two possible franchise projects were cancelled disneys dwarfs and the disney princess enchanted tales line after the first dvd release the june  release of the disney princess palace pets app from disney publishing lead dcp to turn palace pets into a disney princess franchise extension with the release of the palace pets toy line in august from licensee blip toys the line was also listed by timetoplaymagcom for its most wanted list holiday  disney bunniesedit disney bunnies created by disney consumer products original work licensing spinoff print publications books i love you my bunnies thumper counts to ten goodnight thumper miscellaneous spun off from bambi and bambi ii disney bunnies is a disney consumer products spinoff franchise based on thumper from the  film bambi and its  followup bambi ii selected as dcps third franchise to be launched disney bunnies was launched on january   with three books disney dragonkindedit disney dragonkind created by disney consumer products original work licensing spinoff miscellaneous toys statues spun off from disney movies disney dragonkind is a disney consumer products spinoff franchise based on dragons appearing in disney animated movies it was launched in january  with a statue of maleficent from sleeping beauty in dragon form gentle giant studios sculpted the three first statues with the last two being mushu from mulan and elliot from petes dragon dcpi structureedit disney licensing disney retail disney store worldwide inc disney shopping inc online and other direct marketing channels games and interactive experiences dcpi labs team the muppets studio formerly muppets holding company llc dcpi publishing and digital media disney digital networks maker studios polaris gaming channel advanced media disney social disney coop custom content and all platform ad sales disneycom disney style oh my disney disney lol babblecom disney family familycom gocom formerly go network starwarscom and star wars app disney publishing worldwide disney shoppingedit disney shopping inc formerly disney direct marketing disney direct marketing services inc ddm is the direct sales subsidiary of disney consumer products a segment subsidiary of the walt disney company ds historyedit disney direct marketingedit fiscal year sales million    estimated  the walt disney company purchased the childcraft education corporation for  million from grolier inc to expand its mailorder business and that the childrens furniture and equipment area fit with the disney characters target market childcrafts mailing list would boost walt disney family gift catalogs mailing list from  million to  million disney direct marketing services inc was incorporated on may   in  disney stores had started leasing land in the southpoint distribution park in memphis in  disney direct marketing started operating out of a building built there by clayco prior to december  disney direct marketing had sold the playclothes catalog as they did not support the disney brand at that time ddm had a inhouse kansas city telemarketing center and a warehouse in memphis in december  ddms hq was moved from new york city to the main disney campus in burbank california due to the relocation the unit needed to restaff donna bhatia was hired then as disney direct marketing as vice president of marketing and new business development and was involved in the restaffing adding another  hours to her work day the company added its first services then with the pooh gram  gift service the company added its first services in december  with the pooh gram  gift service in may  disney direct marketing was sued over the service for copyright and trademark infringement of vermont teddy bear companys trademark mailorder beargram ideas and logo by october  the case was settled out of court with an agreement that includes changes to reduce confusion also in may  disney sold its childcraft education corp to us office products co for  million disney sold childcraft as the catalog did not support the disney brands bhatia got the disney catalog distributed by the disney stores which had not happen much before which generated sales of  million at lower mailing costs she then found that disney had multiple  customer databases of which only five were used for catalog mailings combined the  databases had  million records that after removing duplicated records consisted of  million households with the unified database disney started adding additional catalogs started in spring  with the walt disney gallery catalog plus two more by june  with the increased sales a new warehouse was being build in south carolina with disneys purchase of the remainder of infoseek in july  the go network infoseek the disney catalog disney online disneycom and disneystorecom abc news internet ventures and espn internet ventures and buena vista internet group are merged into the gocom company disney shoppingedit disney direct marketing services inc had changed its name to disney shopping inc as it operated online with the disneyshoppingcom domain by january   disney shoppings kansas call center was closed with some of the  employees would transferring to a utah call center and few would remain until may  on may   disneyshoppingcom was redesigned and relaunched at a new domain disneystorecom with the additional of disney parks and resorts products catalogsedit disney catalog walt disney gallery spring  a twice a year collectibles catalog which has also been sent to lenox mint danbury mint and franklin mint catalog lists by june   its circulation was  million copies per year and generating  million in annual sales disney kids by july  send to parents twice a year in august focusing on backtoschool and in september focusing on halloween costumes by june   its circulation was  million copies per year and generating  million in annual sales disneystorecom formerly disneyshoppingcom pooh’s corner  for the fans of the bear character by june   its circulation was  million copies per year and generating  million in annual sales playclothes sold by  childcraft april may  educational products servicesedit  gift service pooh gram december   a parent can order a appropriately occasion dressed pooh bear sent with a personal message this service takes in  million in revenue per year mickey gram  pending as of june  club winnie the pooh flag  sends holiday flags on a regular basis which did  million a year in revenue in  referencesedit  a b httpsbusinesssearchsoscagovcbssearchresultssearchtypecorpsearchcriteriadisneyconsumersearchsubtypekeyword  a b c d e company overview of disney consumer products inc investing businessweekcom retrieved  november    a b jarvey natalie february   disneys consumer products and interactive division loses leslie ferraro promotes james pitaro the hollywood reporter retrieved february     ehrbar greg  mouse tracks the story of walt disney records first ed jackson ms university press of mississippi p  isbn  retrieved march     aberdeen j a  disneyland hollywood renegades cobblestone entertainment isbn  retrieved may     a b c hirsch jerry december   winnie the pooh gains momentum across disney product lines the orange county register knight riddertribune business news retrieved  december    leonard devin burke doris january   the curse of pooh fortune time inc retrieved july     disney consumer products inc entity number c business search state of california retrieved  november    vaughan vicki march   disney restaurants to close after l